President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster for the Muscogee (Creek) Nation and authorized federal aid to assist with the recovery efforts from severe storms, straight-line winds, tornadoes, and flooding that occurred between May 7 and June 9, 2019. The federal funding will be available on a cost-sharing basis for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. Benjamin D. Abbott has been appointed as the Federal Coordinating Officer for the recovery operations in the affected areas. Further damage assessments may result in additional designations if requested by the Tribe. For more information, contact the FEMA News Desk.